[Desktop Entry]
Type=Application
Version=1.0
Name=BASTION Dashboard
GenericName=GPU Broker Monitor
Comment=Monitor BASTION's GPU/LLM broker — queues, models, VRAM, alerts
Exec=@LAUNCHER@
Terminal=true
Icon=utilities-system-monitor
Categories=Development;System;Monitor;
StartupNotify=false
Keywords=GPU;LLM;Ollama;Broker;BASTION;Monitor;
# scripts/install-desktop.sh substitutes @LAUNCHER@ at install time. When the
# launcher is scripts/launch_dashboard.sh and a conda env is active at install
# time, the installer bakes `env BASTION_CONDA_ENV=<env>` into the command —
# GUI .desktop launches do not load your shell's conda init, so the interpreter
# must be made explicit or the TUI cannot start.
#
# TODO(window-positioning): With Terminal=true the system picks the user's
# default terminal emulator; placing the resulting window is left to the
# window manager. On GNOME+X11 a per-session wrapper using wmctrl can pin
# the window (e.g. `wmctrl -r "BASTION Dashboard" -e 0,1280,540,640,540`
# after a short sleep). On Wayland this needs a Mutter/GNOME extension
# such as "Auto Move Windows". Not implemented here — manual placement
# until either approach is wired up.
